  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 12 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 3 critical, 5 high, 12 medium, 19 normal. Key bases needing attention include Iaşi (IAS/LRIA), Craiova (CRA/LRCV) and Modlin (WMI/EPMO); plus 5 other bases. 12 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV) and Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR). Network hotspots: Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Federico Fellini (RMI/LIPR), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Gran Canaria (LPA/GCLP) and 7 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, very low visibility and RVR limitations. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Federico Fellini (RMI/LIPR), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Stockholm-Arlanda (ARN/ESSA) and 9 others.",
